obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1352  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"NR2A- but not NR2B-containing NMDAR are required for LTD induction\" (rat cerebellum, Zn antagonist)\nFig.3: NR2A is exclusively located in the parallel fibers varicosities (presynapses)\nFig.4 Electrophysiological characterisation of NR2A overexposed in HEK cells using WC patch-clamp. Shows that the NR2A receptor regulates membrane potential (indrect via voltage-clamp)\n\nTogether these data show that the presynaptic NR2A containing receptor is active at the presynaptic plasma membrane and that here the firing properties of the presynaptic neuron are regulated via modulation of the presynaptic membrane potential to shape LTD induction presumably via Gutamate autoreception.\n\nA model for the presynaptic action of the NMDARs is presented in Fig.5. Experimental description: - Rat tissues are used: \"Experiments were performed on transverse cerebellar acute slices (300 μm) of rats (17- to 24-day-old).\"\n\nNo information on species of cloned receptors: HEK293 cells plated on glass coverslips in 35-mm Petri dishes were transfected with 2" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1352" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

